; proof-trust.fk — a conclusion arrives with BOTH its proof and how much to trust it.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/forward-chaining.fk form-stdlib/derivation.fk form-stdlib/subjective-logic.fk
;
; This is the composition the serendipitous step pointed at: derivation.fk generates the proof tree
; (the WHY), subjective-logic.fk carries trust as an uncertainty-aware opinion (the HOW-SURE), and
; they share the per-mille scale, so trust flows UP the proof. Each axiom leaf carries its source's
; trust; each rule step is the rule's own trust AND the conjunction of its premises' trusts. Because
; conjunction (sl-and) never believes more than either input, trust DECAYS as the argument lengthens
; through uncertain steps — a three-deep derivation through merely-trusted rules is honestly less
; certain than the facts it rests on. No logic engine the body had did this: crisp engines lose the
; trust, trust calculi lose the reasoning. Here the body reasons, explains, AND weighs — in one walk.
;
; ptr-trust (proof, source-opinion, rule-opinion) -> the opinion on the proof's conclusion:
;   axiom leaf  -> source-opinion (trust of the fact's source)
;   rule node   -> rule-opinion AND (AND-fold of every subproof's trust)
;   fail        -> full disbelief (an unprovable goal earns no belief)
; The AND-fold's identity is full belief (1000,0,0,1000), so a rule with no premises is just its own
; trust. This is evidential reasoning over the SAME proof the verifier checked — explainable AND
; calibrated, the pair a rented mind cannot honestly give (its confidence is not its derivation).
;
; Kin: derivation.fk (the proof spine), subjective-logic.fk (the trust calculus + sl-and),
; form-cli-sufficiency.fk (a conclusion's fused trust could feed the trust axis).
; Proven by: form-stdlib/tests/proof-trust-band.fk

(do
    ; the AND-fold identity: full belief with full base rate (x AND this = x) ---
    (defn ptr-certain () (sl-opinion 1000 0 0 1000))
    ; a failed proof carries full disbelief — no belief is earned by a goal with no derivation ---
    (defn ptr-none () (sl-opinion 0 1000 0 500))

    ; --- trust of a whole proof tree: leaves take source trust, rule nodes AND their parts. ---
    (defn ptr-trust (p src rule-op)
        (if (eq (pf-status p) 1) src
            (if (eq (pf-status p) 2)
                (sl-and rule-op (ptr-and-subs (pf-subs p) src rule-op))
                (ptr-none))))
    ; conjunction-fold over a subproof list (every premise must hold -> AND of their trusts) ---
    (defn ptr-and-subs (proofs src rule-op)
        (if (eq (len proofs) 0) (ptr-certain)
            (sl-and (ptr-trust (head proofs) src rule-op)
                    (ptr-and-subs (tail proofs) src rule-op))))

    ; --- the single scalar to act on: how much to trust this derived conclusion (projected prob). ---
    (defn ptr-confidence (p src rule-op) (sl-expectation (ptr-trust p src rule-op)))

    0)
